<p>
phpMyAdmin security announcement
</p>
<hr>
<p>
Announcement-ID: PMASA-2008-7<br />
Date: 2008-09-15<br />
Updated: 2008-09-17 (CVE id)<br />
</p>
<p>
<b>Summary</b>:<br />
Code execution vulnerability
</p>
<p>
<b>Description</b>:<br />
We received an advisory from Norman Hippert and we wish to thank him for his work. The <tt>server_databases.php</tt> script was vulnerable to an attack coming from a user who is already logged-on to phpMyAdmin, where he can execute shell code (if the PHP configuration permits commands like <tt>exec</tt>).
</p>
<p>
<b>Severity</b>:<br />
We consider this vulnerability to be serious.
</p>
<p>
<b>Affected versions</b>:<br />
Versions before 2.11.9.1. 
</p>
<p>
<b>Solution:</b><br />
Upgrade to phpMyAdmin 2.11.9.1 or newer.
</p>
<b>References:</b><br />
<p>
<a href="http://fd.the-wildcat.de/pma_e36a091q11.php">http://fd.the-wildcat.de/pma_e36a091q11.php</a><br />
<a href="http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2008-4096">http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2008-4096</a><br />
In case of questions, please contact the
phpMyAdmin team. Our website is <a href="http://www.phpmyadmin.net">http://www.phpmyadmin.net/</a>.
</p>
